               <msContents>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                     <rubric>Nomina sacra; name of the protagonist; names of the donors.  &#xD;
A few lines in the incipit page of Text I, incipit of Text II, incipits of all sections and its numbers; word sälam; elements of the punctuation signs and text dividers; elements of Ethiopic numerals.</rubric>
                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  <!--The data in the items below refers to other items. please remove this items and move the information to the appropriate place.-->
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <note>Text I ("Vita of Mamas") does not contain the last chapter (kidan-scene) as presented in<ref type="mss" corresp="ESaqm002">AQM-002</ref>(fols. 24va-29ra).</note>
                     <note>In Text II ("Miracles of Mamas") most of the miracles are numbered. The 8th miracle is missing in<ref type="mss" corresp="ESaqm002">AQM-002</ref>. The 12th miracle begins on fol. 38vb l.5. Its explicit differs from the miracle presented in<ref type="mss" corresp="ESaqm002">AQM-002</ref>(fols. 38ra-38vb). Here, ʾabunä Bǝrhan Moʿa is mentioned as commissioner "of this book". Furthermore the 13th miracle ends differently than in<ref type="mss" corresp="ESaqm002">AQM-002</ref>(fols. 42va-43rb) and is followed by an ʾarke-hymn.</note>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
